                          <h2 style="color:#31a400;font-weight:bold;margin-top:10px;">Largest children's English school</h2>
                          <h2 style="font-weight:bold;">January 2019</h2>
                          <p>For its first offshore satellite, Seiha English Academy reached towards the Philippines. The Philippines is globally recognized not just as one of Asia’s top English-speaking countries but as one of the largest English-speaking nations in the world. English has always been one of the country’s official languages and is spoken by more than 14 million Filipinos. Filipinos, being non-native English speakers, but having successfully mastered the intricacies of English on top of being capable of speaking at least 2 dialects (one’s regional dialect and Tagalog) are strategically effective communicators and teachers of English as a Second Language (ESL).</p>
